The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 22: Sebi has asked brokers to get income details such as tax returns, salary slips and bank account statements of the investors every year to check the flow of black money into stocks. Sebi has asked brokers to bar those investors, who do not furnish adequate proof for the source of their funds, from trading in derivatives market.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 22: The fertiliser ministry has proposed to link the floor price of urea with the gas price in the revised policy to allay industry fears over rate fluctuation. The floor price is the minimum production cost that the fertiliser ministry takes into account while reimbursing the subsidy on urea.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 22: Tata group firm Jaguar Land Rover is understood to have geared up to start assembling sports utility vehicle Freelander2 from November at the Chikhli facility in Maharashtra.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 22: The employees of public sector general insurance companies and the LIC will get a 17.5 per cent wage hike with the government nod likely in September. The four PSU insurance firms have submitted the report to the finance ministry on August 17 asking for a 17.5 per cent wage hike, A.K. Singhal, CEO of General Insurance Public Sector Association, said.                                                                                                                          
